# API Examples for Go HRM Services

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost
@userService = {{baseUrl}}:8081
@companyService = {{baseUrl}}:8082
@employeeService = {{baseUrl}}:8083

### User Service - Login
POST {{userService}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "hostname": "example.com",
  "platform": "web",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "internalid": ""
}

### User Service - Refresh Token
POST {{userService}}/api/v1/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..."
}

### User Service - Logout
POST {{userService}}/api/v1/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

### User Service - Health Check
GET {{userService}}/health

### Company Service - Create Company
POST {{companyService}}/api/v1/companies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "domain": "example.com",
  "name": "Example Corporation",
  "owner_id": 1
}

### Company Service - Get Company by Domain
GET {{companyService}}/api/v1/companies?domain=example.com

### Company Service - Get Company by ID
GET {{companyService}}/api/v1/companies/1

### Company Service - Health Check
GET {{companyService}}/health

### Employee Service - Create Employee
POST {{employeeService}}/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "company_id": 1,
  "user_id": 1,
  "internal_id": "EMP001",
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

### Employee Service - Get Employee by User ID
GET {{employeeService}}/api/v1/users/1/employee

### Employee Service - Get Employees by Company
GET {{employeeService}}/api/v1/companies/1/employees?page=1&limit=10

### Employee Service - Health Check
GET {{employeeService}}/health